==English==
===Etymology===
From sal ammoniac, which was first  obtaining near the temple of Jupiter [[w:Ammon|Ammon]], by burning  camel's dung.  See [[Ammoniac]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈmon.jʌ/

===Noun===
# (Chemestry) A gaseous compound of hydrogen and nitrogen, NH<sub>3</sub>, with a pungent smell and taste.  Obsolete names include [[volatile alkali]], and [[spirits of hartshorn]].
